<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-06-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="731" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d731">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Allen</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-06-12"><hi rend="italic">June 12,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 196.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch No. 456, of the 7th ultimo, requesting that you be instructed
                            to accept a substitute <pb facs="0816" n="736" xml:id="pg_736"/>
                            amendment proposed by the Japanese Government, of Article VI of the land
                            regulations for the general foreign settlement of Chemulpo, and to
                            inform you in reply that you may agree to the amendment proposed by
                            Japan.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>